1
00:00:10,688 --> 00:02:10,688
Watch on dramacool.club or kissasia.xyz to support Admin

2
00:00:12,712 --> 00:00:13,847
Junxi.

3
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:22,300
(Episode 10: Love Is a
Secret That Can't Be Hidden)

4
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:33,466
The vibe in here...

5
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:45,145
What am I supposed to do?

6
00:01:55,800 --> 00:02:02,800
"Secret Lover"

7
00:02:03,490 --> 00:02:05,457
If you ever laugh at Tuo
for not having a mom again,

8
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:06,893
I'll kick all your butts.

9
00:02:07,861 --> 00:02:09,696
See if you still dare.

10
00:02:12,298 --> 00:02:13,333
Tuo.

11
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,202
Tuo!

12
00:02:17,937 --> 00:02:19,372
Tuo!

13
00:02:35,355 --> 00:02:36,823
I finally found you.

14
00:02:38,892 --> 00:02:40,859
I chased them all off.

15
00:02:40,860 --> 00:02:42,996
From now on, just hang out with me.

16
00:02:44,030 --> 00:02:45,698
Ignore them.

17
00:02:49,602 --> 00:02:51,937
Maybe it was from that moment on...

18
00:02:51,938 --> 00:02:53,378
that I wanted to always be with him,

19
00:02:55,642 --> 00:02:57,644
to stay by his side.

20
00:02:59,779 --> 00:03:01,647
Running away isn't protecting someone.

21
00:03:01,648 --> 00:03:04,450
One lie leads to a hundred more.

22
00:03:05,318 --> 00:03:07,619
And you end up hurting the
person you want to cherish.

23
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:10,156
Making them anxious and yourself uneasy.

24
00:03:12,158 --> 00:03:14,526
Are you really in such a hurry?

25
00:03:14,527 --> 00:03:16,362
What am I supposed to do?

26
00:03:20,633 --> 00:03:21,701
Junxi.

27
00:03:24,237 --> 00:03:25,672
Dad, Mom...

28
00:03:30,076 --> 00:03:31,076
We...

29
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:33,146
We've known for a long time.

30
00:03:35,114 --> 00:03:36,816
You finally said it!

31
00:03:42,188 --> 00:03:43,656
But I haven't said anything yet.

32
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:46,491
- You haven't?
- Honey, didn't you hear him?

33
00:03:46,492 --> 00:03:47,660
Honey, didn't you hear him?

34
00:03:48,628 --> 00:03:49,962
I was just following your lead.

35
00:03:49,963 --> 00:03:51,330
Didn't we agree?

36
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:52,131
That when Junxi told us

37
00:03:52,132 --> 00:03:53,432
he and Tuo were dating,

38
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:54,466
I was supposed to follow you.

39
00:03:54,467 --> 00:03:55,935
Follow you!

40
00:03:59,539 --> 00:04:00,673
So you've known all along?

41
00:04:04,544 --> 00:04:06,145
And you also knew

42
00:04:06,679 --> 00:04:08,580
that Tuo and I are living together,

43
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:10,383
not just to split the rent,

44
00:04:12,585 --> 00:04:13,585
but as a couple?

45
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:15,020
Of course.

46
00:04:16,222 --> 00:04:17,356
We know

47
00:04:17,357 --> 00:04:19,892
that you're both responsible kids.

48
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:22,795
You wouldn't give us
anything to worry about.

49
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:33,473
Why are you crying?

50
00:04:42,682 --> 00:04:45,652
You must have been worried
we'd disapprove after finding out.

51
00:04:46,486 --> 00:04:48,966
You've been stressing about
this for a long time, haven't you?

52
00:04:49,689 --> 00:04:51,024
I'm sorry.

53
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,697
I'm sorry for lying to you all this time.

54
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:01,833
I just didn't know how to tell you

55
00:05:01,834 --> 00:05:04,336
about my relationship with Tuo.

56
00:05:04,337 --> 00:05:06,306
I was afraid you'd be upset if you knew.

57
00:05:07,507 --> 00:05:09,107
I was afraid that after you found out,

58
00:05:09,108 --> 00:05:10,943
you'd be disappointed in me and Tuo.

59
00:05:12,612 --> 00:05:14,279
It's not his fault.

60
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:16,281
I was the one who told Junxi to lie

61
00:05:16,282 --> 00:05:18,184
and hide the fact that we were dating.

62
00:05:21,888 --> 00:05:23,221
You didn't lie.

63
00:05:23,222 --> 00:05:24,956
You just didn't tell us.

64
00:05:24,957 --> 00:05:26,793
That's different from lying.

65
00:05:28,027 --> 00:05:29,095
Besides,

66
00:05:29,529 --> 00:05:30,796
even though you two didn't tell us,

67
00:05:30,797 --> 00:05:31,963
we already knew.

68
00:05:31,964 --> 00:05:33,099
Yeah, that's right.

69
00:05:35,034 --> 00:05:36,601
Even without you saying anything,

70
00:05:36,602 --> 00:05:38,470
when the two of you are together,

71
00:05:38,471 --> 00:05:39,604
the way you are...

72
00:05:39,605 --> 00:05:41,365
It's like you only have
eyes for each other.

73
00:05:49,082 --> 00:05:51,384
You can't hide it when
you really like someone.

74
00:05:57,323 --> 00:05:58,390
So, after all this time,

75
00:05:58,391 --> 00:05:59,491
I'm the only one in the family

76
00:05:59,492 --> 00:06:01,427
who didn't know you two were dating?

77
00:06:01,994 --> 00:06:03,195
And here I was worried for so long.

78
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:03,930
Mom, look.

79
00:06:03,931 --> 00:06:05,130
I'm getting a bald spot from the stress.

80
00:06:05,131 --> 00:06:06,298
That's what you get for
running away from home.

81
00:06:06,299 --> 00:06:07,233
You deserve it.

82
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:07,967
You deserve it.

83
00:06:07,968 --> 00:06:09,068
Okay, okay, okay.

84
00:06:09,302 --> 00:06:10,822
It'd serve you right if you went bald.

85
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:13,372
Go bald.

86
00:06:18,244 --> 00:06:19,345
You deserve it.

87
00:06:25,485 --> 00:06:28,454
You're serious about my brother, right?

88
00:06:31,457 --> 00:06:32,897
Why are you looking at me like that?

89
00:06:33,292 --> 00:06:34,761
I can scowl too.

90
00:06:35,161 --> 00:06:37,001
If we're going to scowl,
let's do it together.

91
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:40,666
From the moment I realized I liked him,

92
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,134
all I've thought about

93
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:43,469
is being with him forever.

94
00:06:49,575 --> 00:06:50,710
So you want to get married?

95
00:06:56,449 --> 00:06:58,116
Anywhere he is,

96
00:06:58,117 --> 00:06:59,452
that's my home.

97
00:07:00,787 --> 00:07:01,787
This place is too.

98
00:07:04,824 --> 00:07:08,093
Then why are you
scowling at me, your family?

99
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:09,762
You've been scowling since we were kids.

100
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:12,465
Junxi liked you more when we were little.

101
00:07:14,734 --> 00:07:15,967
Of course.

102
00:07:15,968 --> 00:07:17,003
He's my little brother.

103
00:07:17,804 --> 00:07:18,838
Jealous much?

104
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,540
Does Junxi know?

105
00:07:29,649 --> 00:07:30,982
If anything happens,

106
00:07:30,983 --> 00:07:32,063
your big bro has your back.

107
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,955
You little brat.

108
00:07:41,227 --> 00:07:42,728
Stay for dinner tonight.

109
00:07:46,999 --> 00:07:47,967
By the way,

110
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:48,868
when did you and Dad

111
00:07:48,869 --> 00:07:51,070
find out Tuo and I were together?

112
00:07:52,238 --> 00:07:53,638
Your freshman year of college, I think.

113
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:54,806
Right, honey?

114
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:55,874
I think so.

115
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:58,109
That's when you dragged
me to that parenting workshop.

116
00:07:58,110 --> 00:07:59,590
It was to understand our kids better.

117
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:01,646
But...

118
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:03,927
Tuo and I didn't get together
until our sophomore year.

119
00:08:08,421 --> 00:08:10,857
So we were wrong all along?

120
00:08:11,924 --> 00:08:13,391
But, son,

121
00:08:13,392 --> 00:08:15,093
that just means that
before you were even dating,

122
00:08:15,094 --> 00:08:17,162
you already liked him a lot.

123
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:17,697
Otherwise,

124
00:08:17,698 --> 00:08:19,265
how could we have gotten it wrong?

125
00:08:25,972 --> 00:08:27,306
After what your mom said,

126
00:08:28,307 --> 00:08:30,309
I only just realized

127
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:32,777
that I've liked you since way back then.

128
00:08:43,456 --> 00:08:44,957
Why is it so messy in here?

129
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:49,228
Let's clean it up together.

130
00:08:51,731 --> 00:08:53,632
Can we clean it tomorrow?

131
00:08:53,633 --> 00:08:54,667
I've missed you so much.

132
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:02,608
You just said you liked me.

133
00:09:38,811 --> 00:09:40,413
Where is it?

134
00:09:41,047 --> 00:09:42,348
Why has it disappeared?

135
00:09:58,230 --> 00:09:59,465
What are you looking for?

136
00:10:06,505 --> 00:10:07,707
Did I wake you?

137
00:10:10,810 --> 00:10:11,810
It's time to wake up.

138
00:10:12,144 --> 00:10:13,446
We have class this morning.

139
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:15,081
What are you looking for?

140
00:10:17,049 --> 00:10:18,517
The ring you gave me.

141
00:10:19,151 --> 00:10:20,620
I'm sure I put it here.

142
00:10:28,995 --> 00:10:30,029
I put it away.

143
00:10:58,391 --> 00:10:59,824
After we moved in,

144
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:00,926
you never wore it.

145
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:03,362
I thought you didn't really like it.

146
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:24,501
This was one of the things
making you insecure, wasn't it?

147
00:11:32,892 --> 00:11:34,326
Put it on for me.

148
00:11:35,961 --> 00:11:37,930
You don't have to force
yourself for my sake.

149
00:11:44,804 --> 00:11:46,844
I didn't wear it because
I was afraid of losing it.

150
00:11:47,173 --> 00:11:49,040
Also, us wearing matching rings

151
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,361
would attract too much attention.

152
00:11:52,278 --> 00:11:53,278
And later,

153
00:11:53,279 --> 00:11:54,546
if you decided we weren't a good match

154
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:56,047
and wanted to break up,

155
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:56,649
it would be awkward.

156
00:11:56,649 --> 00:11:57,483
We're not breaking up.

157
00:11:57,483 --> 00:11:58,483
Last time...

158
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:02,254
Let me finish.

159
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:06,292
That's what I thought at first.

160
00:12:06,959 --> 00:12:09,594
But when you broke up with me last time,

161
00:12:09,595 --> 00:12:10,930
I realized

162
00:12:11,697 --> 00:12:13,599
I could never break up with you.
(Watch on dramacool.club or kissasia.xyz to support Admin)

163
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:16,900
I already like you so much
that I can't be without you.

164
00:12:19,038 --> 00:12:20,071
Don't say it.

165
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:21,607
I'll never say it again.

166
00:12:32,118 --> 00:12:33,853
We still have class this morning.

167
00:12:34,653 --> 00:12:35,788
Let's skip.

168
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:41,927
After everything last night...

169
00:12:42,328 --> 00:12:43,562
It wasn't enough.

170
00:12:50,269 --> 00:12:51,570
Rock, paper, scissors.

171
00:12:52,538 --> 00:12:53,506
I win.

172
00:12:53,507 --> 00:12:54,640
You go to class.

173
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:04,116
Scissors.

174
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:05,084
Rock.

175
00:13:05,085 --> 00:13:06,185
Paper.

176
00:13:06,886 --> 00:13:07,886
What are you doing?

177
00:13:18,397 --> 00:13:19,898
When we get married,

178
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:21,367
and switch to wedding rings,

179
00:13:22,201 --> 00:13:23,602
only then can you take this off.

180
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:28,107
Also,

181
00:13:28,108 --> 00:13:29,908
don't you dare leave
this ring at home again.

182
00:13:30,976 --> 00:13:32,044
Let go.

183
00:13:33,546 --> 00:13:34,380
No.

184
00:13:34,381 --> 00:13:35,713
Let go.

185
00:13:35,714 --> 00:13:36,881
No.

186
00:13:36,882 --> 00:13:38,551
If you don't let go, how can I hug you?

187
00:13:41,620 --> 00:13:42,720
It's a deal.

188
00:13:42,721 --> 00:13:44,801
We'll save up for our future
wedding rings together.

189
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:55,701
Let's go...

190
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:57,403
Go where?

191
00:13:57,837 --> 00:13:59,371
To class?

192
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,945
Or to bed?

193
00:14:28,934 --> 00:14:31,269
I thought you'd turned into a workaholic.

194
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:34,310
Turns out you were just fighting with
Tuo and trying to distract yourself.

195
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:36,827
I didn't tell you because
I didn't want you to worry.

196
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:40,279
At least it all worked out in the end.

197
00:14:40,512 --> 00:14:42,113
And your aunt and uncle are so supportive.

198
00:14:42,114 --> 00:14:43,616
That's really wonderful.

199
00:14:44,683 --> 00:14:46,084
Tuo and I promised each other

200
00:14:46,085 --> 00:14:47,485
that we'd work hard to
become better people,

201
00:14:47,486 --> 00:14:48,966
so they won't have to worry about us.

202
00:14:49,755 --> 00:14:51,723
And with so many people supporting you,

203
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:53,191
you must be really happy.

204
00:14:53,192 --> 00:14:54,627
Xiao Yang Yang.

205
00:15:00,332 --> 00:15:01,967
Is that my lunch?

206
00:15:03,836 --> 00:15:05,638
I got you two packets of spicy radish.

207
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:08,774
You know me so well.

208
00:15:14,713 --> 00:15:15,848
Han Tuo.

209
00:15:18,784 --> 00:15:20,285
Hold this for me.

210
00:15:20,286 --> 00:15:21,286
Let me see.

211
00:15:28,460 --> 00:15:29,560
Thanks.

212
00:15:29,561 --> 00:15:31,162
Our advisor wanted
me to tell you something.

213
00:15:31,163 --> 00:15:32,730
He's hoping you'll come
back as an industry mentor...

214
00:15:32,731 --> 00:15:33,932
and teach a class at school.

215
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:34,900
I knew it.

216
00:15:34,901 --> 00:15:36,301
Asking me back for another guest lecture...

217
00:15:36,302 --> 00:15:37,836
I knew there was a catch.

218
00:15:39,338 --> 00:15:40,438
Are you really...

219
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:41,440
going to reject me?

220
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:45,644
Han Tuo.

221
00:15:46,645 --> 00:15:48,514
Let's just date, no strings attached.

222
00:16:02,161 --> 00:16:03,195
You like me?

223
00:16:04,096 --> 00:16:05,130
Of course, I do.

224
00:16:06,365 --> 00:16:06,966
Why?

225
00:16:06,967 --> 00:16:09,335
At first, I just thought
you were really talented.

226
00:16:09,902 --> 00:16:11,502
But somewhere along the way...

227
00:16:11,503 --> 00:16:13,872
it started to hurt when I saw you sad.

228
00:16:15,207 --> 00:16:16,941
You don't have to answer right away.

229
00:16:16,942 --> 00:16:18,043
I'll wait for your answer.

230
00:16:23,716 --> 00:16:25,384
I only love Junxi.

231
00:16:30,456 --> 00:16:33,324
Then I'll just have to
wait for your next fight.

232
00:16:33,325 --> 00:16:34,925
And make my move when you're vulnerable.

233
00:16:36,028 --> 00:16:37,429
Even then, I wouldn't choose you.

234
00:16:39,698 --> 00:16:41,700
You deserve someone who truly loves you.

235
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:46,739
What do I do?

236
00:16:47,306 --> 00:16:48,306
I think...

237
00:16:48,307 --> 00:16:49,741
I'm starting to admire
you more and more.

238
00:16:49,742 --> 00:16:51,610
Tuo.

239
00:16:59,952 --> 00:17:01,220
Watch out!

240
00:17:02,988 --> 00:17:04,423
You borrowed this from He Youmei?

241
00:17:05,891 --> 00:17:06,992
We meet again.

242
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,028
Hello.

243
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:15,634
Remember.

244
00:17:15,635 --> 00:17:17,301
The design blueprints are due tomorrow.

245
00:17:17,302 --> 00:17:17,803
Okay.

246
00:17:17,803 --> 00:17:18,803
Let's go.

247
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:26,110
Are you jealous?

248
00:17:29,214 --> 00:17:31,583
Why don't you just tie me
up and keep me at home?

249
00:17:35,621 --> 00:17:36,921
I'll consider it.

250
00:17:36,922 --> 00:17:38,042
You didn't get the hoverboard.

251
00:17:39,124 --> 00:17:40,792
Let He Youmei get it herself.

252
00:17:40,793 --> 00:17:42,561
She almost made you fall.

253
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:46,697
Talk about a double standard.

254
00:17:46,698 --> 00:17:47,899
Looks like Han Tuo's rubbing off on him.

255
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,340
Now he's a total green-eyed monster.

256
00:17:49,802 --> 00:17:51,703
Then how come you're
not becoming more like me?

257
00:17:55,274 --> 00:17:56,108
What did you say?

258
00:17:56,108 --> 00:17:57,042
Nothing.

259
00:17:57,043 --> 00:17:58,443
Xiao Yang, are you getting shy?

260
00:17:58,444 --> 00:18:00,084
- Say that again.
- I didn't say anything.

261
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:15,994
What are you doing here?

262
00:18:23,702 --> 00:18:24,503
Your coffee.

263
00:18:24,503 --> 00:18:25,503
Thank you.

264
00:18:33,645 --> 00:18:35,813
I said I was moving to Kaohsiung.

265
00:18:35,814 --> 00:18:37,382
And you just up and moved out.

266
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:40,318
You even got a part-time
job to support yourself.

267
00:18:40,319 --> 00:18:42,153
You think you're all grown up now, huh?

268
00:18:42,154 --> 00:18:43,454
Why are you so stubborn?

269
00:18:43,455 --> 00:18:44,722
You came all this way...

270
00:18:44,723 --> 00:18:46,091
just to ask me this?

271
00:18:49,495 --> 00:18:50,596
Where are you going?

272
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,734
Between a father and son...

273
00:18:56,735 --> 00:18:58,971
is arguing the only
thing we have left to say?

274
00:19:14,386 --> 00:19:16,487
When I was young,

275
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:18,223
all I knew was how to work.

276
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:22,727
You cried a lot as a baby.

277
00:19:22,728 --> 00:19:24,696
I honestly didn't know what to do.

278
00:19:26,965 --> 00:19:29,034
So I left everything to your mother.

279
00:19:30,435 --> 00:19:32,404
She already had postpartum depression.

280
00:19:33,238 --> 00:19:34,973
But I just kept working.

281
00:19:38,143 --> 00:19:39,911
And that's what led to...

282
00:19:39,912 --> 00:19:41,446
her mental health issues.

283
00:19:46,885 --> 00:19:48,554
Right up until our divorce.

284
00:19:49,488 --> 00:19:51,423
I know I was wrong.

285
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:56,762
But I chose to keep running away.

286
00:20:03,769 --> 00:20:05,603
I always thought...

287
00:20:05,604 --> 00:20:07,405
that providing you
with material things...

288
00:20:07,406 --> 00:20:09,141
could make up for it.

289
00:20:15,247 --> 00:20:16,949
But I was wrong again.

290
00:20:19,418 --> 00:20:21,452
I'm your father.

291
00:20:21,453 --> 00:20:23,222
And I'm the only family you have.

292
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:26,825
I should have been by your side.

293
00:20:31,997 --> 00:20:32,431
I know.

294
00:20:32,431 --> 00:20:33,431
Dad.

295
00:20:40,606 --> 00:20:43,108
I've wired you your living expenses.

296
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:45,477
Um...

297
00:20:46,211 --> 00:20:48,080
How have you been lately?

298
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:53,585
You're up so early.

299
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:56,087
I know I've always been busy with work.

300
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,208
And that I've neglected you.

301
00:20:58,156 --> 00:20:59,190
That won't happen again.

302
00:20:59,191 --> 00:21:00,191
Let's...

303
00:21:00,192 --> 00:21:02,093
move to Kaohsiung together.

304
00:21:02,094 --> 00:21:03,934
We'll have more time
to spend with each other.

305
00:21:05,931 --> 00:21:08,566
I'm sure your father cares about you.

306
00:21:08,567 --> 00:21:10,035
He's worried about you.

307
00:21:11,703 --> 00:21:13,805
He's only saying this for your own good.

308
00:21:47,572 --> 00:21:48,774
Dad.

309
00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:51,194
I'll come visit you in Kaohsiung next time.

310
00:22:12,864 --> 00:22:13,864
Junxi.

311
00:22:14,066 --> 00:22:15,133
Jeff's looking for you.

312
00:22:29,481 --> 00:22:30,682
Come in.

313
00:22:41,126 --> 00:22:42,660
The 'House of Dreams' project...

314
00:22:42,661 --> 00:22:43,781
you did a good job on it.

315
00:22:44,830 --> 00:22:46,797
HR wanted me to ask you...

316
00:22:46,798 --> 00:22:48,165
if you want to keep working part-time.

317
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:50,366
You could become a full-time
employee after graduation.

318
00:22:58,210 --> 00:22:59,910
This is from the day of
the configuration error.

319
00:22:59,911 --> 00:23:01,245
It's the login and
modification log for the system.

320
00:23:01,246 --> 00:23:03,047
And the data from before
and after the change.

321
00:23:03,048 --> 00:23:04,582
Cross-reference them, and you'll see...

322
00:23:04,583 --> 00:23:07,319
who caused 50,000
players to get a free character.

323
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:08,552
Lu Junxi.

324
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:14,578
I'm not the one who keyed it in wrong.

325
00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:28,874
Talking to Jeff like that
will definitely offend him.

326
00:23:29,808 --> 00:23:31,888
You don't want to work
there after graduation?

327
00:23:40,285 --> 00:23:41,853
It's not easy to find a job right now.

328
00:23:43,488 --> 00:23:45,056
I know.

329
00:23:45,624 --> 00:23:47,358
The old me...

330
00:23:47,359 --> 00:23:48,860
might have chosen to stay.

331
00:23:49,828 --> 00:23:51,062
But now...

332
00:23:51,863 --> 00:23:53,164
I don't want to work for a company...

333
00:23:53,165 --> 00:23:55,233
that makes a rookie take the fall.

334
00:23:57,135 --> 00:24:00,372
They might be the top
company in the industry.

335
00:24:02,974 --> 00:24:03,974
But...

336
00:24:04,209 --> 00:24:05,729
I want to find the best fit for me.

337
00:24:09,181 --> 00:24:10,649
It's like dating.

338
00:24:11,783 --> 00:24:13,343
So has 'the best' come looking for you?

339
00:24:14,085 --> 00:24:15,886
That's not the point, is it?

340
00:24:15,887 --> 00:24:17,088
I'm jealous.

341
00:24:19,624 --> 00:24:20,425
Go ahead.

342
00:24:20,426 --> 00:24:21,526
Eat your heart out.

343
00:24:26,998 --> 00:24:28,433
You're the best one.

344
00:24:38,610 --> 00:24:39,311
Boss.

345
00:24:39,312 --> 00:24:41,613
Your workers are so handsome.

346
00:24:42,113 --> 00:24:43,081
They're not my workers.

347
00:24:43,081 --> 00:24:44,049
He's my son.

348
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:46,183
Both of your sons are very handsome.

349
00:24:46,184 --> 00:24:46,885
That's right.

350
00:24:46,886 --> 00:24:48,619
They're both heartthrobs.

351
00:24:48,620 --> 00:24:49,620
Nice.

352
00:24:49,988 --> 00:24:50,956
Our dragon fruit is great too.

353
00:24:50,957 --> 00:24:51,957
Ma'am, come take a look.

354
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,494
My dad just said...

355
00:24:56,495 --> 00:24:57,696
you're his son.

356
00:25:11,543 --> 00:25:12,843
After our internships are over...

357
00:25:12,844 --> 00:25:14,145
let's go on a trip together.

358
00:25:14,613 --> 00:25:15,914
Okay.

359
00:25:30,695 --> 00:25:32,062
I think...

360
00:25:32,063 --> 00:25:33,665
that was the moment...

361
00:25:33,932 --> 00:25:35,092
I started to fall for you.

362
00:25:38,003 --> 00:25:39,137
When was that?

363
00:25:45,877 --> 00:25:47,811
Xiao Yang went to buy ice cream.

364
00:25:47,812 --> 00:25:49,414
What's taking her so long?

365
00:25:53,518 --> 00:25:54,886
Why are you crying again?

366
00:25:55,954 --> 00:25:57,021
Daddy lied to me.

367
00:25:57,022 --> 00:25:58,489
Mommy lied to me too.

368
00:25:58,490 --> 00:26:00,659
Mommy really doesn't want me anymore.

369
00:26:13,805 --> 00:26:15,273
Don't cry, don't cry.

370
00:26:16,341 --> 00:26:18,042
If your mommy doesn't want you...

371
00:26:18,043 --> 00:26:19,678
then you don't want her either.

372
00:26:20,845 --> 00:26:22,680
I'll share my mom with you.

373
00:26:22,681 --> 00:26:24,015
And my dad too.

374
00:26:24,649 --> 00:26:26,183
My brother...

375
00:26:26,184 --> 00:26:27,904
I'll share a little bit of him with you.

376
00:26:28,753 --> 00:26:30,321
What about you?

377
00:26:30,322 --> 00:26:31,523
I'll give you all of me.

378
00:26:36,828 --> 00:26:37,896
Forever?

379
00:26:40,432 --> 00:26:41,432
Forever.

380
00:26:53,411 --> 00:26:55,011
I sold myself off when I was just a kid.

381
00:26:55,580 --> 00:26:56,580
I'm not giving you back.

382
00:26:59,918 --> 00:27:01,352
You're mine.

383
00:27:01,353 --> 00:27:02,687
All mine.

384
00:27:11,730 --> 00:27:13,063
Alright, alright.

385
00:27:13,064 --> 00:27:14,531
I'm yours.

386
00:27:14,532 --> 00:27:16,067
All yours.

387
00:27:19,404 --> 00:27:20,839
Forever?

388
00:27:22,474 --> 00:27:23,775
Forever.

389
00:27:25,543 --> 00:27:27,145
What do you want to do next?

390
00:27:31,549 --> 00:27:33,117
No way.

391
00:27:33,118 --> 00:27:34,385
How about we play rock-paper-scissors?

392
00:27:34,386 --> 00:27:36,426
The winner gets to order
the loser to do one thing.

393
00:27:36,721 --> 00:27:37,455
Okay.

394
00:27:37,455 --> 00:27:38,455
Let's play.

395
00:27:39,124 --> 00:27:39,858
Scissors.

396
00:27:39,858 --> 00:27:40,625
Rock.

397
00:27:40,625 --> 00:27:41,625
Paper.

398
00:27:46,197 --> 00:27:47,465
I win!

399
00:27:49,501 --> 00:27:52,103
Han Tuo, you're so done.

400
00:27:55,273 --> 00:27:56,274
Tuo.

401
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:14,300
Secret Lover - Series Finale
